Add a .env file with the following content:

STANDARD_PASSWORD=<mydefaultpassword>
NEXTCLOUD_URL=<mypublicfacingurl>


Then doing "docker-compose up -d" should do the trick.
Ther certificates for the host must be sorted out
first using certbot, though. I added a manual link 
/var/nextcloud/certbot/conf/live/nextcloud pointing
to the correct directory to hide the URL.

A cronjob should run maintanance periodically:

*/5 * * * * docker exec -u www-data nextcloud-nextcloud php /var/www/html/cron.php >> /root/cron.php.log 2>&1

